1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,660
What if a liquidity pool could play the
World Cup?

2
00:00:03,190 --> 00:00:07,800
This is Mundial, a Uniswap V4 hook on X
Layer.

3
00:00:08,030 --> 00:00:09,840
Mundial does something harder.

4
00:00:10,150 --> 00:00:14,980
It runs the entire tournament with no one
in charge. Here's the trick.

5
00:00:15,350 --> 00:00:18,980
Fans pledge one of eight teams — once,
irreversibly.

6
00:00:19,390 --> 00:00:24,040
When their team's match is live, every
swap they make becomes a shot on goal.

7
00:00:24,450 --> 00:00:26,320
Trading volume scores goals.

8
00:00:26,850 --> 00:00:30,480
The market literally plays the football.
Watch it run.

9
00:00:30,910 --> 00:00:36,340
Argentina versus France. Fans trade. Goals
go up. Five to three.

10
00:00:36,570 --> 00:00:37,840
Argentina advance.

11
00:00:38,470 --> 00:00:42,600
Brazil against England is scoreless into
extra time. Sudden death.

12
00:00:43,130 --> 00:00:46,380
One Brazilian fan swaps. GOLDEN GOAL.

13
00:00:46,890 --> 00:00:49,900
The match settles inside the very swap
that scored it.

14
00:00:50,210 --> 00:00:51,460
Semifinals.

15
00:00:51,570 --> 00:00:53,600
Penalties decided by shot counts.

16
00:00:53,930 --> 00:00:56,620
A final and a champion is crowned.

17
00:00:56,850 --> 00:00:58,480
All of it, hook storage.

18
00:00:59,190 --> 00:01:01,980
Under the hood, one dynamic fee pool.

19
00:01:02,490 --> 00:01:08,140
Fans pay lower fees, a quarter percent
dropping to 0.15 while their team plays.

20
00:01:08,710 --> 00:01:13,500
A 0.2% skim on fan swaps builds the
Champions Pot.

21
00:01:13,990 --> 00:01:16,800
Winning fans claim it pro-rata to their
volume.

22
00:01:17,210 --> 00:01:19,560
Leftovers are donated to the LPs.

23
00:01:20,110 --> 00:01:23,420
No owner, no oracle, no randomness.

24
00:01:23,730 --> 00:01:26,240
The only inputs are swaps and time.

25
00:01:26,410 --> 00:01:28,560
38 tests, fuzzed.

26
00:01:28,910 --> 00:01:33,820
Mundial, live on X Layer, the pool that
plays the World Cup.
